DOCKER DAEMON:
-------------

Docker daemon runs on the host OS.
It is responsible for running containers to manage docker services.
Docker daemon can communicate with other daemons.


DOCKER CLIENT:
-------------
Docker users can interact with docker daemon through a client.
Docker client uses commands and Rest API to communicate with  the docker daemon.
When a client runs any server command on the docker client terminal, the client terminal sends these docker commands to the docker daemin.
It is possible for  docker client to communicate with more than one daemon.


DOCKER HOST:
-----------
Docker  host is used to provide an environment to execute and run applications. It contains the docker daemon, images, containers, network and storages.
